{
  "stem": "27509.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "To get there, he had to go via Russia and Japan to get to Curacao.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this man, on, on a single basis, obtained a transit visa via Russia and obtained a transit visa from the Japanese consul in Kovno.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when he came with these papers and documents stamped [NON-ENGLISH] to go, the, the-- these, these rabbinical students saw a ray of light.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If he can go out that way, why can't we?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All right, we are not Dutch citizens.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we will go as far as we can.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We will-- we will go via Russia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We will go via Japan.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there, maybe we can get to America.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because by that time, the, the American Jewry, and particularly, the rabbinical movement in America, was aware about the plight of this particular yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they wanted to save them en masse to take care of the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that is how the, the fantastic story of the Japanese consul in Kovno, who decided, on his own accord without consulting the foreign office, to issue 10-day transit visas via Japan for people who bought, ostensibly, visas to Curacao, which were equally worthless.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because Curacao had total immigration restrictions.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Nobody could get into Curacao.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he knew it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it was a sufficient formality, on the basis of such an end visa, to obtain a transit visa for 10 days.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's-- and there's a book written about the Fugu Plan-- you may have heard the name about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that is how 2,000 Polish Jews from-- in Wilno have, have managed to obtain such transit visas-- such end visas to Curacao and to obtain a visa via Japan.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then there was one little other thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You had to get from Wilno to Vladivostok, the Trans-Siberian Railways.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
